<strong>Do you want to be part of the next big startup?</strong><br />
360pi is an award-winning price intelligence engine that helps retailers and manufacturers monitor pricing to increase sales and margins and optimize product mix. We help big retailers know exactly what their competition is doing, every day.</p>
<p>
You&#39;re a developer; you want to know what&#39;s under the hood. How about this:<br />
&bull; Advanced artificial intelligence algorithms that pull structured data out of the web<br />
&bull; A 100% cloud based infrastructure<br />
&bull; A NoSQL database that stores a million new price points every single day: Big Data, very Big Data<br />
&bull; A&nbsp; MapReduce based analytical engine for summarizing, slicing and dicing our vast information store<br />
&bull; A web based portal, putting reports and visualizations into the hands of our customers</p>
<p>
We&#39;re building a product using the latest technologies. We need smart people to take it further.</p>
<p>
<strong>Work With Us and Get</strong><br />
&bull; Responsibility: what you do here will have a direct impact on our growth<br />
&bull; Flexible working hours: we focus on results, not punching a clock<br />
&bull; Work remotely: everything we do is in the cloud, so our office is wherever you are<br />
&bull; Great hardware: a Macbook Pro, 27 inch display, SSD<br />
&bull; Location: We&#39;re nestled in Westboro, a great neighbourhood to walk around<br />
&bull; Team activities: climb a wall, spike a volleyball&hellip; we play as hard as we work</p>
<p>
<strong>We Need People To</strong><br />
&bull; Improve and automate our data import and validation capabilities<br />
&bull; Help architect and implement our data transformation architecture<br />
&bull; Keep abreast of the latest in Big Data developments: NoSQL databases, map/reduce, horizontal scalability</p>
<p>
<strong>We&#39;d Like You To Have:</strong><br />
&bull; A keen interest in startups with the desire to take the initiative<br />
&bull; Be self-motivated, really self-motivated, with a &ldquo;customer-first&rdquo; attitude.<br />
&bull; Did we say be self-motivated already? Ever built your own software apps for fun?<br />
&bull; Prior experience in writing database applications in Python, Ruby, Java, or C#.<br />
&bull; An understanding of standard development lifecycle processes and methodologies.<br />
&bull; Basic knowledge of XML.<br />
&bull; Basic knowledge of object oriented programming.<br />
&bull; Experience with databases and schemas<br />
&bull; A degree in computer science, engineering, math, or physics.</p>
<p>
<strong>And It Would Be Cool if You Had:</strong><br />
&bull; Cloud Computing (Google AppEngine, Amazon AWS).<br />
&bull; Experience and/or familiarity with MongoDB or other non-SQL database systems.<br />
&bull; Experience with sub-version, git or other source control system.<br />
&bull; Familiarity with web user experience design principles.<br />
&bull; Experience with cloud computing: Google App Engine, Amazon EC2, Amazon S3.<br />
&bull; Experience in machine learning and data mining algorithms.</p>
<p>
If this sounds like a perfect fit for you, we would love to hear from you!<br />
