We are looking for self-starters that enjoy working in a dynamic environment and are motivated by challenging work. We&rsquo;re creating and marketing a very innovative product into the huge retail market, and we need driven team members who are passionate about creating and launching disruptive new technology.&nbsp; If you are looking for a fast-paced and dynamic work environment, then 360pi is the place for you!</p>
<p>
This is a unique opportunity for a Manager of Finance &amp; Administration / Controller to position themselves at the forefront of their field in a rapidly growing company.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Your responsibilities will include:</strong></p>
<p>
<em>Financial</em></p>
<ul>
<li>
Report to the CEO, but functionally to the company&rsquo;s virtual CFO.</li>
<li>
Maintain the company&rsquo;s financial system (currently Simply Accounting).</li>
<li>
Establish Contract acceptance, Invoicing &amp; Deferred Revenue system.</li>
<li>
Manage the credit &amp; collection system.</li>
<li>
HST filings &amp; compliance.</li>
<li>
Prepare Monthly, Quarterly &amp; Annual Financial Reports.</li>
<li>
Work with and support operational mangers in terms of their F&amp;A requirements.</li>
<li>
Preparation of yearend audit files as required.</li>
<li>
Preparation of support data &amp; documents for the annual Tax Return and SR&amp;ED filings.</li>
<li>
Support Due Diligence effort by potential investors.</li>
<li>
Manage near-term cash flow, including payables management.</li>
<li>
Manage grant/subsidy submissions &amp; compliance.</li>
<li>
Assist in the finalization of the budget &amp; implementation of the budget into the reporting system.</li>
<li>
Functional supervision and mentoring of Finance &amp;&nbsp;Administration staff.</li>
<li>
In collaboration with the CFO and/or CEO, review, source and maintain company insurance policies.</li>
<li>
Assist the CFO and CEO in preparing updates for the Board of Directors, and to current and prospective investors.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>We genuinely would like you to have all of these:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
A college degree or equivalent.</li>
<li>
At least 5 years of accounting experience, of which at least 3 in a knowledge-based industry.</li>
<li>
Strong familiarity with Simply Accounting and/or other PC based accounting packages.</li>
<li>
Strong computer skills including Excel and Word programs and email at a highly proficient level</li>
<li>
Be professional and self-motivated, with extraordinary drive and initiative.</li>
<li>
Be prepared to work part-time or as a consultant for the first 6-12 months.</li>
</ul>
