			<description><![CDATA[<p>
360pi is an award-winning price intelligence platform that helps retailers and manufacturers monitor competitive pricing to increase sales and margins and optimize product mix.</p>
<p>
<br />
Nestled in the trendy Westboro area in Ottawa, we are looking for self-starters who enjoy working in a creative environment and are motivated by challenging work. We&rsquo;re creating and marketing a very innovative product into the huge retail market, and we need team members who are driven and passionate about creating and launching disruptive new technology.&nbsp; If you love demand generation, e-commerce, retail and cutting edge technology, and are looking for a fast-paced and dynamic work environment, then 360pi is the place for you!</p>
<p>
<br />
This is a unique opportunity for a versatile individual to position themselves at the forefront of their field in a rapidly growing company. The perfect opportunity to start a career in marketing or sales. The Lead Development Representative is responsible for generating new business opportunities by engaging with both cold and warm prospects. The successful candidate will research key accounts, follow up with prospects who have shown interest through marketing campaigns, and help educate prospects with relevant content.&nbsp; Working closely with the Marketing and Sales teams, the person in this role will be assigned specific call objectives, including cold calling, in order to assist in creating opportunities for Sales.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Your responsibilities will include:</strong><br />
<br />
&bull; Being proactive, persistent and self-motivated to meet outbound call objectives<br />
&bull; Respond, in a timely manner, to information requests from prospects<br />
&bull; Identify prospect pains and communicate these to marketing, sales and project management<br />
&bull; Facilitate communication of prospect intelligence to marketing, sales and product management<br />
&bull; Learn and maintain an in-depth knowledge of 360pi products and services, industry trends, and competition and record them in our competitive tracking tool<br />
&bull; Keep the marketing database up-to-date and list imports<br />
&bull; Report on marketing campaign performance using Salesforce.com and Marketo<br />
&bull; Educate prospects and facilitate access to educational resources about price intelligence<br />
&bull; Discover, qualify and pass new opportunities to Sales<br />
<br />
<strong>We genuinely would like you to have all of these:</strong><br />
<br />
&bull; Ability to develop relationships with senior-level technical and business decision makers<br />
&bull; Enjoy speaking to people over the phone<br />
&bull; Have a strong interest in technology<br />
&bull; Demonstrated &quot;people&quot; skills, and exceptionally organized with the ability to multi-task<br />
&bull; Strong team player with excellent communication skills<br />
&bull; Proficiency with Microsoft Office products<br />
&bull; Passion for lead generation, marketing, the web, and e-commerce<br />
&bull; Self-motivated, with strong initiative and drive<br />
&bull; Excellent verbal and written communication skills<br />
&bull; Motivated by challenge, and with a strong understanding and liking for the startup experience<br />
&bull; Strong business and task orientation; focused on execution, excels at getting things done<br />
&bull; Ability to work well in a team with others, striving to meet common goals<br />
<br />
<strong>And it would be really cool if you have any of these:</strong><br />
<br />
&bull; University/college degree in business<br />
&bull; Interest in sales/marketing<br />
&bull; Retail marketing experience<br />
&bull; Experience with SalesForce, Jigsaw or Marketo</p>
